method.name: current_size
method.description: The number of people currently in the party, must be at least 1.

method.name: id
method.description: Specifies the id of the party. "Party" is used colloquially to refer to a group of players in a shared context. This could be a lobby id, server id, team id, etc. All party members should specify a RichPresence update using the same party id so that the Discord client knows how to group them together. If specified, must be a string between 2 and 128 characters.

method.name: max_size
method.description: The maximum number of people that can be in the party, must be at least 0. When 0, the UI will not display a maximum.
